Package: crownsegmentr
Title: Tree Crown Segmentation in Airborne LiDAR Data
Version: 0.4.4
Authors@R: c(
    person("Leon", "Steinmeier",
        role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), 
        email = "Leon.Steinmeier@posteo.net",
        comment = "Created the package as part of his master thesis."),
    person("Nikolai", "Knapp", 
        role = c("aut", "cph"), 
        email = "Nikolai.Knapp@ufz.de",
        comment = "Initialized and motivated the development of the package and provided an R draft of the AMS3D algorithm."))
Description: Provides a function that performs the adaptive mean shift algorithm
    for individual tree crown delineation in 3D point clouds as proposed by 
    Ferraz et. al, 2016.
